<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css" />
    <title>Profile</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #E5D9F2;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: auto;
            background: #9B7EBD;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px #000000;
        }
        h3 {
            color: #000000;
            margin-top: 30px;
        }
        .flower-info {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            padding: 10px;
            border: 1px solid #F7F9F2;
            border-radius: 5px;
            background-color: #F7F9F2;
        }
        img {
            max-width: 100%;
            height: auto;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        a {
            color: #C4E1F6;
            text-decoration: none;
        }
        a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }
        p {
            color: #555;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h3>The Most Common Flower</h3>
        <div class="flower-info">
            <h4>Roses</h4>
            <p>Roses are perhaps the most popular flower in the world. Known for their beautiful petals and fragrant aroma, roses symbolize love and passion. They come in various colors, each representing different emotions. For example, red roses signify deep love, while yellow roses convey friendship.</p>
            <img src="https://example.com/rose.jpg" alt="Roses" />
        </div>

        <div class="flower-info">
            <h4>Tulips</h4>
            <p>Tulips are elegant flowers that bloom in spring, showcasing a vibrant palette of colors. These flowers symbolize grace and beauty. They are often associated with perfect love and can be gifted on various occasions to express admiration and affection.</p>
            <img src="https://example.com/tulip.jpg" alt="Tulips" />
        </div>

        <div class="flower-info">
            <h4>Sunflowers</h4>
            <p>Sunflowers are bright and cheerful, known for their large, sunny yellow petals. They symbolize adoration, loyalty, and longevity. Sunflowers are unique in that they turn to face the sun, making them a perfect representation of positivity and joy.</p>
            <img src="https://example.com/sunflower.jpg" alt="Sunflowers" />
        </div>

        <a href="/auth/logout">Logout</a>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
